[b]Smooth Trend Radar[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Takes the Supertrend indicator one step further: instead of using the bands directly for a binary signal, this script averages the upper and lower Supertrend bands into a midline and then applies a double smoothing pass (WMA followed by EMA). The result is a baseline that changes direction far less frequently than standard Supertrend — trend direction is determined by whether this baseline is rising or falling, not by price crossing the bands.

[b]Features[/b]
[list]
[*]Double-smoothed Supertrend midline (WMA → EMA) — significantly fewer whipsaws than standard Supertrend
[*]Slope-based trend detection: bullish when the baseline rises, bearish when it falls
[*]Rejection counter: fires a signal when price touches the baseline for N consecutive bars — identifies consolidation before continuation
[*]Automatic SL/TP levels on each trend flip: entry, stop loss, and three take profit targets as labeled horizontal lines
[*]Risk/reward fills: semi-transparent fill between entry and SL (red) and entry and TP3 (green)
[*]Direction-aware alerts for flips, rejections, TP hits, and SL hits
[/list]

[b]How to read it[/b]
[list]
[*]Baseline color: green = uptrend, red = downtrend
[*]Up/down label on the baseline = trend flip entry signal
[*]Small triangles above/below bars = rejection signals (price touching baseline without crossing)
[*]Horizontal lines at flip = current SL and TP1/TP2/TP3 levels
[/list]

[b]Settings to tune[/b]
[list]
[*]Supertrend Factor and ATR Period control the width of the underlying bands — larger values produce a more stable, slower baseline
[*]WMA and EMA lengths control the smoothing — higher values reduce noise but increase lag
[*]Consecutive Bars (rejection) controls how many touches are needed before a rejection signal fires
[/list]

